in order to entertain the public.

517
00:30:33,039 --> 00:30:35,041
That'd be a variety show,
not a documentary.

518
00:30:35,124 --> 00:30:38,753
You could just watch shows like
I Live Alone.

519
00:30:38,878 --> 00:30:42,298
You've lost your touch.
Our job is to film what's real.

520
00:30:42,382 --> 00:30:45,093
It is also our job to get
what's real out of them, isn't it?

521
00:30:48,263 --> 00:30:50,098
I still can't get my head around it.

522
00:30:50,348 --> 00:30:52,976
Since when did we work
only after we got our head around things?

523
00:30:53,393 --> 00:30:56,062
Until when will you stay jobless?
It's time you start working.

524
00:30:56,145 --> 00:30:59,148
I'll produce and cast So-min.

525
00:30:59,232 --> 00:31:00,358
It's your call now.

526
00:31:03,403 --> 00:31:04,404
Come on.

527
00:31:19,460 --> 00:31:21,504
DRESSING ROOM
LEE SO-MIN

528
00:31:49,991 --> 00:31:52,327
Pizza will get cold. Eat this too.

529
00:31:52,410 --> 00:31:54,203
Eat up, Min-jun.

530
00:32:00,543 --> 00:32:02,503
What is it? What's wrong?

531
00:32:03,838 --> 00:32:06,132
-So-min.
-Yes, Min-jun.

532
00:32:06,257 --> 00:32:08,635
There's no way you'd feel full
by watching others eat.

533
00:32:08,718 --> 00:32:10,845
Yes. It is possible.

534
00:32:10,929 --> 00:32:13,348
Look. I already feel full.

535
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:17,185
No.

536
00:32:17,268 --> 00:32:19,896
It only works when your love
surpasses everything else.

537
00:32:20,313 --> 00:32:24,025
For example, when parents
watch their children eat.

538
00:32:24,484 --> 00:32:26,694
When farmers watch the field get watered.

539
00:32:26,778 --> 00:32:29,989
When the actress watches her manager
eat carbohydrates.

540
00:32:30,907 --> 00:32:34,619
I love you dearly. I'm so full right now.

541
00:32:36,871 --> 00:32:40,291
Just eat if you're going to lose yourself.
You're too skinny now.

542
00:32:40,667 --> 00:32:44,379
You're not shooting any dramas
these days anyway. Just eat.

543
00:32:44,462 --> 00:32:47,382
Hey, stop burning your carbs
and eat already.

544
00:32:47,465 --> 00:32:48,925
I said I'm full.

545
00:32:59,310 --> 00:33:03,147
What do you say?
Shall I dip this in the sauce?

546
00:33:03,648 --> 00:33:06,025
Oh, right. You should. Dip a lot.

547
00:33:06,109 --> 00:33:09,112
I'll just cover the pizza with the sauce.

548
00:33:11,280 --> 00:33:12,615
What about the chicken?

549
00:33:20,748 --> 00:33:22,041
How about some sausage?

550
00:33:24,168 --> 00:33:25,044
Okay.

551
00:33:33,678 --> 00:33:35,722
I'm so full.

552
00:33:36,431 --> 00:33:38,349
My stomach is about to burst.

553
00:33:44,272 --> 00:33:45,732
What? Why?

554
00:33:46,983 --> 00:33:49,610
-I am curious.
-Why? What?

555
00:33:50,153 --> 00:33:52,447
Hello.

556
00:33:52,530 --> 00:33:53,740
Right now, I'm...

557
00:33:53,823 --> 00:33:55,033
-Is that so?
-Hello.

558
00:33:55,116 --> 00:33:58,119
-Hey, you're here.
-Hi.

559
00:33:59,328 --> 00:34:02,373
Did you take a good rest?
Let's not take any breaks today.

560
00:34:02,457 --> 00:34:04,167
Why would you worry about such things?

561
00:34:04,250 --> 00:34:07,670
-How can I not?
-You're so cute.

562
00:34:07,754 --> 00:34:09,005
-You're scary.
-Hello.

563
00:34:09,088 --> 00:34:11,382
-Hey, you're here.
-Hello.

564
00:34:11,466 --> 00:34:13,426
-He's so handsome.
-Thank you.

565
00:34:13,509 --> 00:34:15,678
-Hi, Il-jung.
-Hello.

566
00:34:15,762 --> 00:34:17,013
Can I call you by your name?

567
00:34:17,638 --> 00:34:19,098
Sure.

568
00:34:19,849 --> 00:34:22,977
Why are you blushing? You must be happy.

569
00:34:25,605 --> 00:34:29,358
-Am I blushing?
-No. You're just dull.

570
00:34:31,194 --> 00:34:32,570
You seem tired.

571
00:34:32,653 --> 00:34:34,655
-I know.
-Not all actresses are like her.

572
00:34:34,739 --> 00:34:36,616
She's just extraordinary, right?

573
00:34:36,699 --> 00:34:38,242
She sure seems interesting.

574
00:34:38,326 --> 00:34:40,995
Wouldn't it look too much like
a commercial approach though?

575
00:34:41,871 --> 00:34:43,998
It's fine as long as
you don't approach it that way.

576
00:34:44,832 --> 00:34:47,085
Even if I manage to film reality,
it'll still look fake.

577
00:34:47,168 --> 00:34:48,669
You haven't said you'd do it yet.

578
00:34:48,753 --> 00:34:51,964
Right.
I can say no if I don't want to do it.

579
00:34:52,840 --> 00:34:55,093
Ms. Lee, I'll put your mic on you.

580
00:34:55,176 --> 00:34:57,428
-Oh, okay.
-Please do us a favor.

581
00:34:57,512 --> 00:34:59,305
Look at the director's face.

582
00:34:59,931 --> 00:35:02,975
His heart failed while he was editing
last week's episode.

583
00:35:03,059 --> 00:35:05,520
He now looks like a zombie, doesn't he?

584
00:35:05,728 --> 00:35:08,147
Oh, okay. Don't worry.

585
00:35:08,731 --> 00:35:09,732
Thank you in advance.

586
00:35:18,991 --> 00:35:21,869
All the panelists are ready.
You can start when you are.

587
00:35:32,130 --> 00:35:33,881
Okay. Good job!

588
00:35:34,715 --> 00:35:38,010
-Good job.
-Good job.

589
00:35:40,847 --> 00:35:42,390
Good job, sir.

590
00:35:42,473 --> 00:35:44,225
Ms. Kim, when did you get here?

591
00:35:44,308 --> 00:35:47,562
I came to say hello.
I got here earlier and watched.

592
00:35:48,813 --> 00:35:52,150
Oh, we didn't leave you out on purpose.
You know that, right?

593
00:35:52,233 --> 00:35:54,610
We wanted to have both you and Ms. Lee
on the program.

594
00:35:54,694 --> 00:35:57,572
I had to leave for my situation.
Don't worry.

595
00:35:57,655 --> 00:35:59,073
Did it go well today?

596
00:35:59,157 --> 00:36:00,324
Well, yes.

597
00:36:00,575 --> 00:36:03,411
I'm not sure if the two made a deal.

598
00:36:04,036 --> 00:36:05,955
It's kind of awkward
because they didn't argue.

599
00:36:08,541 --> 00:36:09,375
Hey.

600
00:36:12,587 --> 00:36:15,298
-Why are you so nice to me today?
-Is that a problem?

601
00:36:15,381 --> 00:36:16,757
Why didn't you get aggressive?

602
00:36:16,924 --> 00:36:19,719
I'm not aggressive. I'm defensive.

603
00:36:19,886 --> 00:36:21,512
You kept nitpicking me last time.

604
00:36:21,596 --> 00:36:24,849
I didn't. I corrected your mistakes.

605
00:36:26,058 --> 00:36:28,144
You think everything is crooked
except for yourself.

606
00:36:28,936 --> 00:36:30,855
No. Just you.

607
00:36:30,938 --> 00:36:34,525
Gosh, my actress. It's getting late.
Let's go.

608
00:36:35,693 --> 00:36:37,403
We're not late. I have nothing else to do.

609
00:36:37,820 --> 00:36:40,198
The traffic will get worse now.

610
00:36:41,490 --> 00:36:43,784
Eun-jeong, I'm going to talk
to the writers.

611
00:36:43,868 --> 00:36:46,412
-Okay, I'll be in the green room.
-Okay.

612
00:36:47,288 --> 00:36:49,957
So-min doesn't have a temper.

613
00:36:50,041 --> 00:36:52,251
She's just like a little kid
who throws a tantrum.

614
00:36:52,376 --> 00:36:55,171
It's kind of funny to play along with her.

615
00:36:58,674 --> 00:37:00,218
Aren't you going to talk to the writers?

616
00:37:00,301 --> 00:37:01,385
I'm done.

617
00:37:01,469 --> 00:37:02,678
That was quick.

618
00:37:02,762 --> 00:37:04,347
You could've texted them instead.

619
00:37:19,028 --> 00:37:20,905
There are so many cars already.

620
00:37:21,197 --> 00:37:23,824
Do you know why the Olympic-daero
is always jammed?

621
00:37:24,533 --> 00:37:25,743
I don't think I'll guess it right.

622
00:37:26,577 --> 00:37:29,497
Because the Olympics is a festival.

623
00:37:29,580 --> 00:37:32,124
I knew it. I couldn't have got that.

624
00:37:32,583 --> 00:37:35,294
-What do you want me to do? Laugh?
-No.

625
00:37:35,795 --> 00:37:37,129
Thanks for putting up with me.

626
00:37:37,213 --> 00:37:38,714
What is it? What's gotten into you?

627
00:37:38,798 --> 00:37:40,883
-What do you mean?
-Why are you cheering me up?

628
00:37:40,967 --> 00:37:42,468
It's making me more anxious.
Don't do that.

629
00:37:42,802 --> 00:37:45,137
I feel like I bullied you
with food earlier.

630
00:37:45,221 --> 00:37:47,598
Don't realize your faults.
That's weird. It makes me more anxious.

631
00:37:47,682 --> 00:37:49,934
I know you always sacrifice yourself.

632
00:37:50,476 --> 00:37:51,769
I'll just be aware of it.

633
00:37:53,813 --> 00:37:55,564
Will you sacrifice yourself for once?

634
00:37:56,691 --> 00:37:59,026
What do you want? I'll do it just once.

635
00:38:01,362 --> 00:38:03,030
I want to go to a Korean restaurant

636
00:38:03,614 --> 00:38:06,033
and eat a meal with you.

637
00:38:07,118 --> 00:38:09,412
Not just me. With you.

638
00:38:27,013 --> 00:38:28,180
Let's see how we go.

639
00:38:28,264 --> 00:38:29,765
Okay. I'll start.

640
00:38:29,849 --> 00:38:30,850
One.

641
00:38:36,397 --> 00:38:37,398
I'm sorry.

642
00:38:37,815 --> 00:38:38,733
A-RANG

643
00:38:38,816 --> 00:38:40,443
Who is it? Is it a guy?

644
00:38:40,526 --> 00:38:42,403
-No, it's a woman.
-Answer it then.

645
00:38:43,612 --> 00:38:46,449
I think I'll have to take this. I'm sorry.

646
00:38:53,831 --> 00:38:56,375
-Hello?
-It's been a while, Hyo-bong.

647
00:38:56,459 --> 00:38:58,294
Hi, A-rang. What's up?

648
00:38:59,628 --> 00:39:03,174
Well, it's about Eun-jeong.

649
00:39:03,758 --> 00:39:05,134
Is she still the same?

650
00:39:05,217 --> 00:39:07,636
Oh, you mean...

651
00:39:10,181 --> 00:39:13,642
-Yes. I'm keeping my eyes on her.
-Okay.

652
00:39:14,477 --> 00:39:16,937
It must be hard for you. I'm just worried.

653
00:39:17,396 --> 00:39:18,689
I'm thinking about what to do.

654
00:39:19,023 --> 00:39:20,024
Okay.

655
00:39:20,441 --> 00:39:21,859
All right, then.

656
00:39:22,526 --> 00:39:24,236
I'll think about it too.

657
00:39:24,487 --> 00:39:26,947
Okay. Thanks, A-rang.

658
00:39:27,031 --> 00:39:29,533
All right, let's talk in person
another time.

659
00:39:29,825 --> 00:39:30,743
Okay.

660
00:39:37,249 --> 00:39:38,334
Let's take a ten-minute break.

661
00:39:39,085 --> 00:39:40,961
No, it's fine.

662
00:39:45,633 --> 00:39:48,302
Hyo-bong, why do you look so down?

663
00:39:48,636 --> 00:39:50,679
Is it from a girl you like?

664
00:39:51,305 --> 00:39:52,640
Do you like girls now?

665
00:39:56,477 --> 00:39:58,479
My sister's friend is a screenwriter.

666
00:39:59,021 --> 00:40:01,357
And she's working
with Director Son Beom-su.

667
00:40:02,066 --> 00:40:03,567
I don't know why,

668
00:40:03,651 --> 00:40:05,403
but she says whenever he hears
the song you wrote,

669
00:40:05,486 --> 00:40:07,113
he becomes extremely depressed.

670
00:40:07,196 --> 00:40:08,322
Oh, right.

671
00:40:09,865 --> 00:40:12,410
It's been really long
since you dated someone, right?

672
00:40:14,412 --> 00:40:15,621
Let's play.

673
00:40:16,122 --> 00:40:17,415
One, two.

674
00:40:31,846 --> 00:40:32,680
So,

675
00:40:33,264 --> 00:40:35,015
where will the guitar pop up from
this time?

676
00:40:35,599 --> 00:40:38,018
I won't play it while I eat.
I'll have to use my mouth and hands.

677
00:40:38,102 --> 00:40:40,104
Then we should talk while we eat.

678
00:40:40,187 --> 00:40:42,398
Go on. I'll sing the whole song
after we're done eating.

679
00:40:42,481 --> 00:40:43,732
I heard enough.

680
00:40:44,150 --> 00:40:47,278
Are things better now
that you've teased me enough?

681
00:40:47,695 --> 00:40:48,863
Let's not be...

682
00:40:49,321 --> 00:40:52,116
so awkward anymore, okay?

683
00:40:53,033 --> 00:40:54,326
Okay.

684
00:40:55,703 --> 00:40:56,787
Hello.

685
00:41:04,962 --> 00:41:06,172
Hello, Ms. Lim.

686
00:41:07,548 --> 00:41:08,549
Hi.

687
00:41:12,970 --> 00:41:14,096
Hello.

688
00:41:15,806 --> 00:41:17,558
-Hello, Mr. Son.
-Hi.

689
00:41:26,275 --> 00:41:27,359
-Da-mi.
-Yes?

690
00:41:27,443 --> 00:41:29,236
I thought my mom came up
with this week's menu.

691
00:41:29,320 --> 00:41:33,782
Your mom must have fed you good food.
That's why you've become so upright.

692
00:41:34,658 --> 00:41:36,619
You think so?

693
00:41:38,621 --> 00:41:40,372
So I'm an upright man.

694
00:41:41,332 --> 00:41:42,750
Am I that upright?

695
00:41:43,167 --> 00:41:45,669
Yes, you are.

696
00:41:48,255 --> 00:41:49,632
You're so upright, Mr. Kim.

697
00:41:50,007 --> 00:41:53,302
You would've made a great teacher.

698
00:41:59,433 --> 00:42:00,559
Yes, sir.

699
00:42:04,188 --> 00:42:05,189
Pardon?

700
00:42:07,399 --> 00:42:09,401
No, I'll go to your office.
Give me a moment.

701
00:42:10,444 --> 00:42:12,071
I'm downstairs. Yes.

702
00:42:12,530 --> 00:42:14,073
-Did something bad happen?
-No.

703
00:42:14,281 --> 00:42:16,075
Ms. Lim, I'll have to go upstairs
for a minute.

704
00:42:16,158 --> 00:42:19,078
Can you stay with Hwan-dong?
I'll be quick.

705
00:42:22,623 --> 00:42:24,166
This is so awkward.

706
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:27,628
Well...

707
00:42:33,717 --> 00:42:36,971
So Ms. Jung won't work here
if we air Ms. Lim's work?

708
00:42:38,556 --> 00:42:41,850
Come on. It's so childish
that I don't even know what to say.

709
00:42:41,934 --> 00:42:44,853
Hey, I heard Ms. Lim was
Ms. Jung's assistant.

710
00:42:45,563 --> 00:42:47,565
Even I'd feel like shit.

711
00:42:48,274 --> 00:42:50,025
It must be like

712
00:42:50,109 --> 00:42:52,653
her boyfriend having an affair
with her daughter and leaving home.

713
00:42:52,736 --> 00:42:55,155
That's some twisted analogy.

714
00:42:55,281 --> 00:42:56,615
We had different thoughts,

715
00:42:56,699 --> 00:42:58,867
and I only came across with
Ms. Lim's work after that.

716
00:42:59,159 --> 00:43:01,287
Whether that's the fact or not,

717
00:43:01,579 --> 00:43:04,373
it'd be hard for Ms. Jung
to see it the same way.

718
00:43:05,416 --> 00:43:06,834
Just work on something else.

719
00:43:07,084 --> 00:43:09,378
It didn't win an award
at our writing contest.

720
00:43:09,503 --> 00:43:11,255
We have no reason to produce it.

721
00:43:11,338 --> 00:43:12,923
I'm the reason, sir.

722
00:43:13,299 --> 00:43:14,300
I'm Son Beom-su.

723
00:43:14,383 --> 00:43:15,884
And I'm Sung In-jong.

724
00:43:17,011 --> 00:43:18,220
And we work at JBC.

725
00:43:19,555 --> 00:43:22,808
The organization does not follow
the decision made for an individual.

726
00:43:22,891 --> 00:43:25,144
You're saying you'll follow
Ms. Jung's decision though.

727
00:43:25,227 --> 00:43:28,606
Ms. Jung will become a free agent
after this drama.

728
00:43:28,939 --> 00:43:31,942
A lot of companies are offering her
long-term contracts.

729
00:43:32,026 --> 00:43:35,654
It'll have been for nothing
if we let others take her.

730
00:43:36,071 --> 00:43:37,156
What about me?

731
00:43:38,532 --> 00:43:40,367
Will you trample on me
for the sake of her pride?

732
00:43:40,451 --> 00:43:42,703
No matter how competent a writer is,

733
00:43:42,911 --> 00:43:45,664
a writer is an outsider
but you're our staff.

734
00:43:45,789 --> 00:43:48,208
Do you think an organization would
ditch our staff

735
00:43:48,292 --> 00:43:49,793
just to hold onto a profitable outsider?

736
00:43:49,960 --> 00:43:50,961
Yes.

737
00:43:52,296 --> 00:43:53,422
Well, it's true.

738
00:43:54,340 --> 00:43:57,051
Gosh, what should we do then?

739
00:43:59,595 --> 00:44:00,804
Let's have a meeting.

740
00:44:00,888 --> 00:44:02,848
The revised script for episode three
will be ready soon.

741
00:44:02,931 --> 00:44:04,183
Ms. Lim and I will

742
00:44:04,266 --> 00:44:06,477
go to the meeting
with the decision-makers.

743
00:44:06,727 --> 00:44:07,811
We'll do a presentation.

744
00:44:07,895 --> 00:44:09,855
We'll show you how competitive
this piece can be

745
00:44:09,938 --> 00:44:11,982
and why we must air it on JBC.

746
00:44:12,566 --> 00:44:13,692
You can decide then and there.

747
00:44:14,735 --> 00:44:17,071
A meaningful work can't be
rejected by a TV station

748
00:44:17,154 --> 00:44:18,656
because of a silly battle of pride.

749
00:44:19,948 --> 00:44:21,784
JBC can do better than that.

750
00:44:24,286 --> 00:44:25,663
I'll think you got what I mean.

751
00:44:42,471 --> 00:44:43,639
You like this.

752
00:44:44,223 --> 00:44:45,641
Don't act like you know.

753
00:44:46,058 --> 00:44:47,559
I only pretended to like it.

754
00:44:48,519 --> 00:44:50,437
In fact, I pretended to be okay with it.

755
00:44:51,021 --> 00:44:54,274
I've always liked the one
where you have 31 flavors to choose from.

756
00:44:56,777 --> 00:44:59,321
You pretended to be okay for seven years?

757
00:44:59,571 --> 00:45:03,200
Yes. That's why I don't think about you.
It only gives me wrinkles.

758
00:45:03,575 --> 00:45:05,119
Do you see the wrinkles on my neck now?

759
00:45:05,202 --> 00:45:06,662
This will get me more.

760
00:45:07,204 --> 00:45:09,039
You had wrinkles even when you were young.

761
00:45:09,331 --> 00:45:10,833
I said, don't act like you know me.

762
00:45:10,999 --> 00:45:13,127
What do you know about my neck wrinkles?

763
00:45:16,338 --> 00:45:18,882
Right, I don't.

764
00:45:20,884 --> 00:45:24,346
Anyway, thanks for deciding
to work with me nevertheless.

765
00:45:24,638 --> 00:45:27,933
It's about my survival.
You don't need to thank me.

766
00:45:28,225 --> 00:45:31,437
It's not like you'll support me
financially. You never did.

767
00:45:44,158 --> 00:45:45,826
Do you still hate me?

768
00:45:45,909 --> 00:45:47,786
I heard that means you're not over me.

769
00:45:48,912 --> 00:45:51,957
I hate you because
